  "texts": [
    "This is because of notable terms like bibliometrics, thematic analysis, content analysis, systematic review, review (suggest review analysis), social media, Twitter, reddit, electronic health records, questionnaire (indicates data source), depression, anxiety, COVID-19 pandemic, mental health, vaccines, coronavirus, malaria (suggest public health), public opinion, public attitude, emotion, and sentiment (suggest sentiment analysis).",
    "Thus, these terms in cluster 3 can be profiled as \"review analysis, data source, sentiment analysis & public health\".",
    "This cluster affirms the popular use of social media as data source.",
    "Unsurprisingly, Covid-19 is a popular theme amongst the public health terms.",
    "• Figure 12 (in appendix) shows the terms in cluster 4 and can be profiled as \"natural language processing\"."
